parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Weld Seam Corrosion and Flaking
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and flaking of the fuel tank weld seams can cause fuel contamination, leading to clogged fuel filters and pumps, resulting in engine stalling, loss of power, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: grey or white flaky material in the fuel tank
dark powdery metallic flakes in the fuel tank.
